natural solution: In symbols, we want the sum of the positive integers $k$ such that $$\dfrac23 < \dfrac k{27} < \dfrac89.$$ Multiplying the expressions in these inequalities by $27$, we have $$18 < k < 24.$$ The integer solutions are thus $k = 19,20,21,22,23$, which add up to $5\cdot 21 = \boxed{105}$.
